==Versions suitable for calculators==
The approximation
formula_53
and its equivalent form
formula_54
can be obtained by rearranging Stirling&#x27;s extended formula and observing a coincidence between the resultant power series and the Taylor series expansion of the hyperbolic sine function. This approximation is good to more than 8 decimal digits for with a real part greater than 8. Robert H. Windschitl suggested it in 2002 for computing the gamma function with fair accuracy on calculators with limited program or register memory.

