<doc id="151825" wikidata="Q16869854" url="?curid=151825" title="Esquirol">
<text>Esquirol means &quot;scab&quot; (strikebreaker) in Spanish, and &quot;squirrel&quot; in Catalan and Occitan. It is also a surname and may refer to:

* Jean-Étienne Dominique Esquirol (1772–1840), French psychiatrist
* John H. Esquirol (1900–1970), American Episcopal bishop
* Joseph A. Esquirol (1898–1981), New York politician

==See also==
* Charenton (asylum), commonly referred to as the &quot;Esquirol Hospital&quot;
* L&#x27;Esquirol, a municipality in Catalonia</text><links>
